    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't it kind of a slippery slope though? if we judge every intervention just on whether it stopped a immediate crisis, even if it leaves a country in complete ruin for decades, doesn't that basically justify any kind of regime change? like, is there a point where the \"humanitarian\" justification stops being a legitimate strategic goal and just becomes an excuse for interventionism?",
